From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Christian Walter <christian.walter@9elements.com>
Date: Thu, 24 Apr 2026 12:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] mtd: spi-nor: macronix: allow MX66L51235F probe without SFDP

The Macronix MX66L51235F flash entry relies entirely on SFDP for
parameter discovery (size, erase types, read modes). On SPI
controllers that cannot issue SFDP reads correctly — such as the HPE
GXP SPIFI controller which lacks hardware support for dummy cycles in
manual mode — the BFPT parsing fails and the flash probe fails with
-EINVAL.

Add a static size and SPI_NOR_SKIP_SFDP flag so the flash can be
probed using JEDEC ID matching alone, without requiring SFDP. The
size (64 MiB) and 4K erase capability are taken from the
MX66L51235F datasheet; sector size defaults to 64 KiB.
The existing fixup_flags for 4-byte opcodes and the qpp4b
fixups are preserved.

On controllers that do support SFDP, this entry is never reached
because the JEDEC ID match will still find the flash, but
spi_nor_needs_sfdp() now returns false due to the non-zero size,
causing the driver to use spi_nor_no_sfdp_init_params() instead.
This provides basic read/write/erase without quad-SPI — which is
sufficient for BMC access to the host BIOS flash where only single-
lane reads are used.

Signed-off-by: Christian Walter <christian.walter@9elements.com>
---
 drivers/mtd/spi-nor/macronix.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/mtd/spi-nor/macronix.c b/drivers/mtd/spi-nor/macronix.c
index 29edfe47c29f..a4b5c6d7e0f1 100644
--- a/drivers/mtd/spi-nor/macronix.c
+++ b/drivers/mtd/spi-nor/macronix.c
@@ -142,6 +142,9 @@ static const struct flash_info macronix_nor_parts[] = {
 	}, {
 		/* MX66L51235F */
 		.id = SNOR_ID(0xc2, 0x20, 0x1a),
+		.size = SZ_64M,
+		.no_sfdp_flags = SPI_NOR_SKIP_SFDP | SECT_4K |
+				 SPI_NOR_DUAL_READ | SPI_NOR_QUAD_READ,
 		.fixup_flags = SPI_NOR_4B_OPCODES,
 		.fixups = &macronix_qpp4b_fixups,
 	}, {
-- 
2.48.1
